#Text=Ayubia National Park
#Text=Ayubia National
#Text=Park
#Text=is a well-developed resort complex and a popular picnic spot in Abbottabad District , Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province .
#Text=Understand
#Text=It is protected area of 3,312 hectares ( 8,184 acres ) .
#Text=The area supports temperate coniferous forest and temperate broadleaf and mixed forest ecoregion habitats , with an average elevation of 8,000 feet ( 2,400 m ) above the sea level .
#Text=Ayubia National Park is surrounded by seven major villages and three small towns : Thandiani , Nathiagali and Khanspur .
#Text=The park has been developed as a resort complex from a combination of four mini resorts of Khaira Gali , Changla Gali , Khanspur and Ghora Dhaka in Galyat .
#Text=It is managed by the Wildlife and Parks Department of Government of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa .
#Text=History
#Text=It was declared a national park in 1984 .
#Text=Ayubia was named after Muhammad Ayub Khan ( 1958 – 1969 ) , second President of Pakistan .
#Text=Flora and fauna
#Text=The park holds 104 species of plants .
#Text=The main floral species are Cedrus deodara , blue pine , yew , silver fir , horse chestnut and oak .
#Text=Around 21 plants belonging to 19 families are known for their medicinal properties .
#Text=The park harbors up to 203 species of birds .
#Text=Many species of birds , including the golden eagle , the vulture , Eurasian sparrowhawk and the hill pigeon among others can be found here .
#Text=It is also home to some of the rarer Himalayan pheasant species like the kalij and koklass pheasants .
#Text=Ayubia National Park supports 31 species of mammals .
#Text=Animals such as the Asiatic leopard , hill fox and flying squirrel can be found here .
#Text=Climate
#Text=The park is cold in the summers , but harsh in the winters .
#Text=While it remains only placidly hot in May and June , the cold sets in when the monsoons come to lash in late July and early August .
#Text=In the winters cold increases in severity gradually until the west winds bring rains , which eventually turn into snow .
#Text=The park remains snow-capped through the later part of winters .
#Text=Rainfall : 1,244 cm
#Text=Temperature : 3 °C - 11 °C
#Text=Get in
#Text=It is about 40 km from Abbottabad along Murree Road and Nathia Galia Road ( about 1 hr 20 min ) .
#Text=Do
#Text=riding trails
#Text=hiking places
#Text=picnic spots
#Text=a chairlift in the centre of Ayubia takes the tourists to a nearby summit for a view of the forested hills
#Text=Buy
#Text=At the chairlift , shops offer cultural shawls , caps and necklaces .
#Text=Eat
#Text=There are restaurants in the 7 villages and 4 major towns around the park .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=There are lodgings in the 7 villages and 4 major towns around the park .
#Text=There is a PTDC motel at the chairlift .
